// A `for` loop body may be a bare statement (no surrounding `{ }`): a single
// `yield` (or `exit`, or a bare expression) is allowed directly. Here
// both the producer and the squaring filter use brace-free `yield` bodies; the
// pipeline still frames each value, so the squares of 0..4 are 0,1,4,9,16.
fn Int square() Int {
    for (&0) |in| yield in * in
}

{ for (0..5) |i| yield i } | square
